\end{align*}where $F_{1}$ is the force of gravity acting on the more massive star and $F_{2}$ is the force of gravity acting on the less massive star. Since the equation is equal to zero, the magnitudes of the forces acting on the stars are equal.  \begin{align*}
F_{1}&=F_{2}\\
\frac{G(2m)m}{x^{2}}&=\frac{Gm(2m)}{y^{2}}\\
\frac{1}{x^{2}}&=\frac{1}{y^{2}}\\
x&=y
\end{align*}Since $x=y$, we can substitute $x$ for $y$ in the first equation to obtain  \begin{align*}
